paragraphs.title: Register auth events as table so we can query
Normal User
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql


select from_unixtime(timestamp/1000,'YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm') as time, min(distinct_auth_attempts) as attempts, min(distinct_auth_attempts_median) as attempts_median, min(distinct_auth_attempts_stddev) as attempts_stddev, min(distinct_auth_attempts_median + 5* distinct_auth_attempts_stddev) as min_stddev from auth_events where auth_orientation = 'LogOn' and user = '${user}' and distinct_auth_attempts is not null group by time order by time

paragraphs.title: Anomalous User
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.sql


select from_unixtime(timestamp/1000,'YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm') as time, min(distinct_auth_attempts) as attempts, min(distinct_auth_attempts_median) as attempts_median, min(distinct_auth_attempts_stddev) as attempts_stddev, min(distinct_auth_attempts_median + 5* distinct_auth_attempts_stddev) as min_stddev from auth_events where auth_orientation = 'LogOn' and user = '${user}' and distinct_auth_attempts is not null group by time order by time
